[Course_Description]
In the world of privacy, the federal and state governments of the United States have overlapping authority. As a privacy professional, you're charged with helping organizations tackle the conflicts created by this patchwork of laws. In this course, Mike Chapple delves into various state privacy laws, as covered by the fifth domain of the IAPP Certified Information Privacy Professional/US (CIPP/US) exam. Mike covers state-specific laws covering data security, data breach notification, and marketing and financial information. Plus, he shares strategies for protecting social security numbers (SSN) in an organization, as well as how to garner support for an SSN protection program. After completing this course, you'll be prepared to answer questions from the State Privacy Laws domain of the CIPP/US exam.